subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia (
Fig. 48
):

Gonocoxite compact, wide, and short, with short apical projection extending medially; bearing numerous strong setae and evenly setulose. Gonocoxal apodeme extending on both sides of aedeagus to form strongly sclerotized structure. Gonostylus ovoid, with numerous strong setae and otherwise evenly setulose, bearing crescent-shaped apical tooth. Aedeagus cylindrical, same width throughout length, tapered at apex. Hypoproct wide at base, divided into two lobes apically by notch of variable size: deep in some individuals, very shallow in others (
Fig. 49
), setose and setulose, with one long seta apically on each lobe. Cerci separated to or almost to base, bulbous, strongly setose and setulose throughout.
